Oct 8 2009 	Nice location	Jockey Club is in the ideal location in Vegas -- directly next to the Bellagio and within walking distance of all other attractions. After reading other reviews, we asked for a room with a view and did receive one to where our window faced the fountains at the Bellagio, it was great!The actual place itself was not great. The Jockey Club is a typical timeshare to where it is roomy and spacious and &quot;appeared&quot; clean. The rooms are very outdated and definitely need a face lift. The tiles in the shower and the flooring are old and need to be replaced. The kitchen is old and the sink/faucet need to be replaced.The biggest disappointment was the pool. The pool area was covered and NO sunlight was able to come through. It was 100+ degrees all week and we were not able to use the pool!!At the time we were there, they were under major construction adjacent to the Jockey Club. This construction prohibited utilizing the main walkway and you had to walk under a covered &quot;construction&quot; walkway to gain access to the main strip. Overall, the Jockey Club is a great location and is NOT a casino -- you are able to go back at night and escape the ringing noises/smoke filled atmosphere. Definitely think the Jockey Club needs revamped and add additional amentities (shuttles, restaurant/deli, pool that is usable, etc.) if they expect to continue to attract time share holders.	
