Sep 1 2009 	perfect location and service	First part of the trip was for business; the second was for play. The Jockey Club was the perfect place for both. Large suite with full kitchen (range, fridge, dishwasher, microwave). Free and fast wifi. Room was clean and comfortable. Room location does make a difference, however. The first room we were assigned faced the Bellagio. Nice view, but also noisy due to the construction traffic. Asked for a quieter room. The staff quickly complied and we were assigned to the top floor. No view, but the quiet was worth the trade off. With the exception of the concierge (who seems clueless), the staff were friendly and efficient. The location is perfect, right in the center of the strip. The construction is a mild annoyance, but didn't really affect us. The Jockey Club is a great value. We'll definitely stay there the next time we're in Las Vegas.	
Aug 30 2009 	Fabulous	It's got the best location possible, it's clean, and has everything you need and more. Construction: I almost changed the reservation as it got closer to our stay because I was fearful of the construction issue. But we didn't change. Don't be scared off because of the construction. Yes the place has gotten swallowed up by construction on 3 sides, but the worst is over. It's still ongoing but most of the outside work on the building next door is done. We heard dump trucks at 6AM each morning but that was the extent of any noise. Our room faced the Bellagio fountains. When you check in, be sure to request a room on the North side so you can enjoy the view. Otherwise, your view may be of a wall.Room: It's the most clean place I've stayed in. Quality of the place is comparable to a Marriott. Double doors from the living/kitchen/dining area to the bedroom. Ours was a 1 bedroom suite. Kitchen had every utensil you could need and was fully stocked with dinnerware and cookware. Stove, fridge, dishwasher, and microwave were spotless. So was the bathroom. Very pleased.Location: The walkway from the street to Bellagio is steps away. Planet Hollywood is directly across the street and Paris is next door to PH. By the way, PH's buffet is highly recommended for breakfast and dinner. Excellent location to walk in either direction - up to MGM Grand or down to Ceasers, the Venetian, etc. There's a covered construction walkway from the street to the entrance. It's lit very brightly at night. Service: Their mini mart is like a 7-11 and had many more things than I expected (like meats). You may not need to go to the grocery store (they have a shuttle to a grocery at least every other day). You can check out movies for free and watch them on DVD in your room - but who wants to do that in Vegas? Beware of the concierge - they also are timeshare reps because the Jockey Club is a timeshare hotel. They called our room and tried to get us to take the hotel tour and offered all sorts of free tickets to shows and discount coupons. If you know what you want to do in advance and try to bargain with them, they may get you free show tickets if you take the timeshare tour. Overall, it was a fantastic stay and I'll recommend this hotel to everyone. We'll likely stay there again next time.	
