Oct 27 2007 	Surrounded by construction!	We had our family reunion this year in Vegas and based on a previous stay at The Jockey Club decided to stay here again. You can't beat the location, right on the Strip next to The Bellagio and across fromPlanet Hollywood (formerlly The Aladdin) and in the past it's been a great place to stay, BUT...where once there was a parking lot and an empty lot is now being transformed into a new resort and casino. TheJockey Club is literally surrounded by the new resort and the construction proves it! The good: Location, valet parking is offered for guests as there is no longer parking on-site, staff are very helpful (and probably a bitembarrassed by all the activity surrounding the hotel), no nonsense nice place to stay while in Vegas.The bad: You are surrounded by construction! We stayed in room 608, a two bedroom/two bath, and could have reached out the master bedroom window and high-fived the construction workers. Yes, they really were that close. Construction (jack hammers, welding, etc.) starts at 6am on all days except Sunday. Over this past weekend (Oct 20-21) they were pouring cement 24/7. Granted, when we meet in Vegas it's to have fun and not relax in our room but after a night of fun and rolling in at all hours, being jolted awake at 6am was not ideal.The pool is heated and, based on past experiences, is a nice place tospend a few hours. Now a large tarp covers the pool area to prevent any construction materials from falling into it or on you! Eak! I chose not to swim this time around...All in all...if you're heading to Vegas to party round the clock and you just need a place to crash before you head out the next day, thenthis might be ok for you. If you're heading to Vegas to play a bit and relax a bit and want to spend some time in your room, then I wouldn't recommend staying here until the construction is completed.	
