Aug 17 2006	inside its ok	We had read the trip advisor reviews about the Jockey Club before we went and were very concerned about the reported building work going on. We had decided before we got there that if it lived up to its reports we would check out and pay to go in one of the strip hotels. However, when we arrived we asked to be put on the side of the hotel away from the noise. We ended up with a huge suite overlooking the Bellagio on the 9th floor. We went to bed late and got up early. We had ear plugs ready anyway, asmy husband is a snorer! so I can honestly say in the week we were there we weren't affected by noise in our room. It was a different matter by the pool. Luckily it wasn't a sunbathing holiday for us and we had little time for pool relaxation, but the time we did sit by the pool was an experience not one to be repeated. If you have an Ipod and can listen to some music you will be ok, the pool is clean and refreshing and there are comfotable beds to lie on, mostly empty because of the noise. Overcrowding wouldn't ever be a problem here! The suite was exceptional, if we wanted to we could have cooked a 3 course dinner for ourselves every night. The kitchen was very well equipped. The dining room table already set when we arrived. It was so welcoming. We had clean towels and maid service every day as we wanted. You can leave a Do not disturb sign out if you don't want the housekeeper coming in. The comfort in the room was like home, lovely plump sofa, big TV in bedroom and lounge, sound system, although we didn't have time to bother. The bed was so big and comfy, good pillows, alarm clock, walk in wadrobe, fab bathroom with new soaps, shampoos, conditioner everday. A wonderful view over the Bellagio fountains and the Eiffel Tower at Hotel Paris. The staff were friendly, as were the other guests. Everyone seemed determined to respect everyone elses space, maybe because of the chaos outside! the bellhops and valets were great guys especially. If you want a taxi you need to walk around to the Bellagio, takes 3 mins to get there. There is a little shop in the club, adequate for essentials. Although if you hire a car and plan to drive out of town anywhere I'd advise getting a decent map from somewhere else other than the shop on sight. The club is in a great position for walking to most of the strip hotels. Circus Circus was a little too far in the heat, but we walked regularly down to the Venetian and Mirage. 15-20 min walk. On the other side we walked to Mandalay Bay, Luxor and that group. Again no more than 15-20 min brisk walk. If possible, I'd advise walking, as a foreigner you get so much atmosphere from being on the street. Its crowded( in August ) and noisy, but people were polite and queued and we loved the sights and smells. Some hotels even pump fragrance out ! Back to the Jockey Club, if you can forget the outside, interior corridors and make sure you get a room facing the Bellagio then its a perfect place to stay. Comfort, clean, space and good service. We'd go back again.	
