May 18 2006	Mixed feelings about this place.	Booked our stay through Expedia. Couldn't beat the price, and the place was nextdoor to the Bellagio where my daughter was staying and getting married. The place was pretty much empty. Understandable as I'm sure the massive construction project going on to the south drives alot of folks away. Rented a car after arriving at the airport. Nearly impossible to find the hotel at night as the sign on top from the south was not lit. Nor was the small sign out front lit. Found the place only by the grace of God and step by step directions provided by my daughter via cell phone. Approach from the north going south and turn after the lakes of Bellagio. Drive slow and live with the honks and you'll find the little,hidden drive to the back of the place where you will drop your car off to a valet. There is no parking lot. Valet service is free and cars are parked at the Aladin. You enter the place through a makeshift rear entrance as the original enttrance on the southside is a construction zone.Our booking, though made weeks in advance found us with a room on the fith floor and facing the construction project. These guy work 24 hours! They also do not disconnect the back-up alarms on the construction equipment at night. So we had our rest punctuated throughout the night by the constant din of beep beep beep beep beep beep beep beep beep beep....you get the point. The midnight shift is made up of a small crew of welders. The whole crew arrives and fires up the big stuff at 5:30 AM. Why oh why could the staff not place guests on the southern side of the complex? It was entertaining though when at another construction site next door across the road broke out the TNT to make digging easier.I could feel the spirit of dead mobsters who may have kept rooms here to enjoy their second lives away from home with their &quot;other women&quot;. Dig the seventies? You'll be right in your element in your room. Where'd they park my Gremlin? This place needs an update! STAT!The pool was acceptable. The spa was interesting when some Mexicans in their underwear joined us. We left, never to venture back. Felt like I was sitting in their washing machine. Also the all the crane booms &quot;parked&quot; around the second story outdoor pool was less then desirable to look at.On the plus side, the complimentary free computers in the lobby were sweet. Very fast connections and convieniance. I've paid up to $9.00 for 15 minutes use at other places. The little store next to the front desk offers enough products to make dining a little more affordable during your stay. The valet service was prompt,friendly and considerate. We felt safe and secure during our three day stay.Overall a more interesting experience then a horrible one. The big plus the Jo offered was price and close location to my daughter at the Bellagio. Our next visit to LV will find us staying elsewhere.	
