May 11 2006	The Jockey Club - Great location great stay!	My wife and I stayed there 5/2 - 5/9, and we loved our room. It was on the 10th floor and had a direct view of the Bellagio fountains. The room was very clean, and when we arrived the table had even been set. This is a timeshare suite, so comes with a fridge, stove and coffeemaker, with a small store downstairs to buy basic food items. The JC also arranges for a free shuttle to a local grocery store, in case you want to cook a lot of your meals in the room. The pool is small by LV standards, but was never crowded, and the gym and hot tub were both of a decent size. The hospitality suite downstairs was a crowning touch, as it had complimentary coffee (if you didn't feel like making your own, I guess), and boardgames and DVDs you could borrow for free. The location is absolutely perfect and I would really recommend this hotel for families.There was a lot of construction going on, but there is construction going on everywhere in LV. Once, we were woken up by a dumpster being loaded at six in the morning, but we were enjoying everything else so much that we just didn't care and went back to sleep. There was also a near-snafu with our reservation, as we called ahead to let them know we'd be checking in three days after our original date (but we had the room for eight days anyway), however our reservation still got placed with the &quot;no-shows&quot;. I probably should have demanded a new confirmation number instead of a &quot;no problem sir&quot;, but if that's the type of room I get for being a &quot;no-show&quot; then I might use that strategy every time!	
