Apr 9 2006	Good value - We Recommend the Jockey Club	We stayed for two nights in a two-bed, 1.5 bath on the south side (facing the construction site) and had a very enjoyable stay. The Staff was friendly and responsive, although with the construction, there was some confusion when the time came to deliver the car (valet only at the Jockey Club). The area on the north side to which the cars are delivered, combined with intermittent construction traffic on the narrow access road cause some jams when getting cars and trying to exit the hotel. The location is excellent, as other reviewers have noted.The only possible downside might be that the rooms are a bit dated, but we didn't think that to be a significant issue. The rooms were clean and the place was well-kept up. There was smoking on our floor, so that could be annoying but we noticed only in the hallway, not in the room.Our room was very clean and well-lit; it could sleep eight with 3 full-size (queen?) beds and a roll-away. We'd heard horror stories from other reviewers about bad service and rooms and the noise with the construction. We couldn't identify with any of those complaints, really. From a value standpoint, at least with prices being what they were during spring break, The Jockey Club blew away everything else we looked at - no question. We had an enjoyable stay and would recommend the Jockey Club.	
