May 19 2005	Great Place to Stay	We stayed at the Jockey Club on the 28th of April for an entire week. I would recommend this place to anyone. The views were great and we were walking distance to everything. The rooms were very nice and the place was very clean. Housekeeping was available everyday with fresh towels, soap and shampoo. We did not have a rental car to go to the grocery store but the Jockey Club does run a shuttle service on Tuesdays that runs to the grocery store and back to the hotel. I can honestly say that I had no complaints about the place except that if you bring 6 people the only shower is in the master bedroom. It would be great if there was a shower in the half bath so that the people in bedroom do not get disturbed. The hotel also supplied free coffee, popcorn and internet use.	
May 18 2005	quiet...great location	My boyfriend and I stayed at the Jockey Club from May 11-16, 2005. The location is perfect, right in the middle of the strip. A very short walk through the parking lot to the strip and the fountains at Bellagio. There is a bus stop right at the end of the parking lot if you want to go to other areas (everything looks so close, but is actually a pretty far walk.) We found the 24 hour bus passes to be a great investment while we were there. As other people mentioned, this is a good place to stay if you are looking to really experience the city and just need a place to sleep or take a break or a swim before going back out on the town. Our room had a full kitchen, which was great in the morning to have some breakfast before leaving for the day. The pool is very small, but it was never crowded...we went for a swim every day around suppertime and only once shared the pool with other people. We enjoyed the fact that we were not in a casino, we rarely seen anyone in the hotel and it was VERY QUIET...(got in at 6am the one night and didnt hear a thing until 1pm when we awoke.) IF however you are looking to go somewhere first class or be waited on hand and foot, this is not the place for you. You would be better off to pay the $300.00-$400.00 per night and stay next door at the Bellagio. Overall we had a great time, and would probably stay here again. The location and price couldn't be better!!	
