Feb 3 2004	loved	Four of us went last year to Las Vegas for a convention. We were on a budget. Also we were co-workers. I liked it because it gave us privacy from each other. Also since we were all on a budget, we couldnt really go out and eat, we were able to cook and just stay in the room till our next meeting. Plus we drove from California and we didnt have to worry about parking or driving while we were there. Also you are right on the strip so if you have a couple of hours to kill you can walk anywhere. We really liked it and we are planning on going again this year to the convention and staying at The Jockey Club.	
Jan 23 2004	missing the glitz - but great for condo type	Visited in January 2003, 2 couples from different towns wanting to rehash old times shared a 2 bedroom. It was very clean and spacious, nothing elaberate but nice to relax, coffee, cocktails, snacks, etc. Pool and grounds not exciting, but it was January. Very centrally located, easy walk over to Bellagio for a cab - much quicker. Great for the price - miss the glitz feeling and the middle of the night gambling - but its right outside your front door everywhere........(try for the front tower - closer to the strip)	
Dec 29 2003	3 Star Quality	This hotel is above average for the price but is not real stylish or immaculant like some of the hotels in Vegas. I stayed here in 2000 in a two-bedroom two-bath suite. We go to Vegas about 2-3 times a year and we prefer to stay in time share units as to basic hotel rooms because of the price. These units are clean, have full kitchens w/dining, big bedrooms and the view is ok. It is next too the Bellagio and walking distance to MGM and NYNY. Pool is ok, not great in anyway. No beautiful grounds. Pretty basic but great price for the rooms!	
Dec 8 2003	We would recommend the Jockey Club	We found the Jockey Club to be situated in an excellent position on The Strip, next door to Bellagio and set back from the road. The room was very nice, although the view we had was overlooking a new road being built and early morning we could hear the lorries reversing(emitting a beep-beep noise). This was a little offputting at the time. Unfortunately the swimming pool was being renovated during our first week (it was a good job we were in Vegas for two weeks). If we wanted to swim we had to walk across The Strip to Polo Towers - which we felt was too much of an effort. We would also comment that the Jockey Club appeared to be a hub for touting time share sellers. Every day a black bus would arrive with people who were being shown around the Jockey Club and being taken somewhere into the Nevada Desert to view newly built or 'to be built' time share apartments. Overall we found our stay at the Jockey Club to be very good and would recommend it - and Las Vegas...........WE LOVE IT!!!!!	
